1. System Modules
apt: Manages packages on Debian-based systems (like Ubuntu).

Example: apt: name=nginx state=latest
yum: Manages packages on RedHat-based systems (like CentOS).

Example: yum: name=nginx state=latest
service: Manages services (start, stop, restart, enable).

Example: service: name=nginx state=started enabled=yes
user: Manages users on a system.

Example: user: name=john state=present
group: Manages groups on a system.

Example: group: name=developers state=present
command: Runs commands on remote systems.

Q1. Difference between command module and shell module

Example: command: ls -l /home
shell: Runs shell commands on remote systems.

Example: shell: echo "Hello, World!"
hostname: Sets the hostname of a system.

Example: hostname: name=webserver
timezone: Configures system time zones.

Example: timezone: name=UTC
cron: Manages cron jobs.

Example: cron: name="backup" minute="0" hour="2" job="/usr/bin/backup"
2. File/Directory Management


     Q2. Difference between COPY and FETCH module
	 Q3. When we use template module
	 
copy: Copies files to remote systems.

Example: copy: src=/path/to/local/file dest=/path/to/remote/file
template: Copies and processes Jinja2 templates to remote systems.

Example: template: src=nginx.conf.j2 dest=/etc/nginx/nginx.conf
file: Manages file and directory properties (permissions, ownership).

Example: file: path=/tmp/example.txt owner=root group=root mode=0644
synchronize: Synchronizes files and directories to/from remote systems.

Example: synchronize: src=/local/dir dest=/remote/dir
3. Cloud Modules
ec2: Manages EC2 instances in AWS.

Q. Please read ping module
Example: ping:

5. Database Modules
mysql_db: Manages MySQL databases.



6. Application Deployment
git: Manages Git repositories.

Example: git: repo=https://github.com/user/repo dest=/path/to/dir
docker_compose: Manages Docker Compose applications.

unarchive: Extracts files from archives (e.g., tar, zip).
Example: unarchive: src=/path/to/archive.tar dest=/path/to/dest/

debug: Prints debug messages.

Example: debug: msg="This is a debug message"

wait_for: Waits for a condition to be met, such as a port being open.

Example: wait_for: host=localhost port=80 state=started
register: Saves output from a task for use in subsequent tasks.

Example:
yaml
Copy
- name: Get disk usage
  shell: df -h
  register: disk_usage
  
8. Package Management
pip: Manages Python packages.

Example: pip: name=ansible state=latest

npm: Manages Node.js packages.

Example: npm: name=express state=latest


Example: lineinfile: path=/etc/hosts line="127.0.0.1 myhostname"
replace: Replaces text in a file.

Example: replace: path=/etc/config.something regexp="old_value" replace="new_value"

2. synchronize module:
The synchronize module is typically used to synchronize directories between the local and remote machines. It uses rsync in the background, making it more efficient for copying 
large directories and for handling directory structures.


